<br>
On the other side of the coin are those who feel that *reputation* is more important than *standing*, and they are certainly two different things.  Your standing, if based on loot and level only, is like judging a person by their salary and the car they drive.  Reputation is based on how you interact with others, how you got where you are, and how you earned what you have.  Once you feel that you have a high enough standing, you no longer need to care about your reputation, right?  If I can be lvl 60, kill the hardest mobs in the game, and have the best gear possible, why should I care how I got there or what people think of me?  My standing will be among &quot;the best&quot;, even if I have to walk all over everyone to get there.<br>
<br>
Reputation be damned, as long as my standing is better than the guy next to me.<br>
<br>
