<br>
I was reading up on some new changes and came across this today. <br>
<br>
The following are going to be perm changes to Everquest as dictated by the spirit of the IGB.<br>
<br>
1.Every char will start out at lvl 60. Since time and work is an issue with some of our customers, we feel it's unfair to make people level up as it would imply some players are better than others skillwise.<br>
<br>
2.No class shall be better than another. All classes will have the exact same hp's, ac and stats. We will make all caster spells identical as to not allow a class to have a better spell than another. We hope this will finally resolve wizard's bitching about how shitty their class is. <br>
<br>
3.All char will start out with the best armor and weapons in the game. We will also remove all equip except the best and will no longer upgrade equip in the future. This will resolve poorly equiped char's jealousy of uber guilds and even the playing field among all players.<br>
<br>
4.No mob will be more difficult than another mob. We no longer wish a mob's death to be based on skill. We just want everyone to have an equal chance at the encounter and being able to defeat it. Mobs will no longer drop loot, therfore dropping the incentive uber guilds would have at killing it. this way,everyone will have (in our eyes) equal chance at engaging that mob.<br>
<br>
5.Guild system will now be abolished. Because the new &quot;spirit&quot; of Everquest is driving for equality and tolernace of less skilled players, we at sony interactive, feel guilds imply a mob mentality of us vs them , we are better than you. Players will also all have the exact same name. &quot;Default_EQPlayer&quot;. We don't wish those who can't think of a good name to feel inadequate. <br>
<br>
We hope you will enjoy these new changes. we know grazel will.<br>
